{
  "texts": [
    "In Fig. 7(b), we show the spin polarization in the large J/t 0 limit, where a simple picture emerges.",
    "The electron localizes in a site i 0 and the magnetization is coherently transferred back between the localized spin and the electronic spin.",
    "This picture is supported by the following argument: The oscillations at large J/t 0 are controlled by a frequency ω = J, while the beating behavior observed without disorder is increasingly suppressed.",
    "C. Absence of thermalization 1.",
    "Absence of thermalization in the S z total = (L -1)/2 sectorWe return to the case of clean systems with W = 0."
  ]
}